cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "ITU and Mathematical Physics: A Single-Axiom View of Lie Groups, Integrable Systems, Yang-Mills, Conformal Field Theory, Index Theorems, Knot Theory, Random Matrix Theory, and Clay Millennium Connections"
message: "If you use this work, please cite it as below."
type: software
authors:
  - family-names: Terada
    given-names: Munehiro
    affiliation: Roboken
    email: munehiro.terada@roboken2.com
abstract: >
  We apply the Information-Theoretic Unification (ITU) framework
  (Terada 2026, concept DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20109209; current latest
  Tier 0 v3.0 at 10.5281/zenodo.20200156) to mathematical physics.
  This is Tier 1 paper #24, the eighth paper of Block A, introducing
  K_math = K_sym ⊕ K_int ⊕ K_gauge ⊕ K_CFT ⊕ K_index ⊕ K_knot ⊕
  K_random, completing the MATHEMATICAL FOUNDATION BLOCK with #17
  K_geom (DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20230667), #19 K_cosmic (DOI
  10.5281/zenodo.20233952), #20 K_field (DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20234703),
  #21 K_stat (DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20237082), #22 K_solid (DOI
  10.5281/zenodo.20249191), #23 K_flow (DOI 10.5281/zenodo.20249794)
  — physics + mathematics in 7 fundamental K-states. The ITU polytope
  reaches 24 vertices with #17-#24 all attaining degree 23 (new
  maximum). Pass-1 progress: 174 of 220 phases (79.1%).
  Phase 167 establishes Lie group structure: Cartan's classification
  (4 families A_n, B_n, C_n, D_n + 5 exceptional E_6, E_7, E_8, F_4,
  G_2; E_8 dim 248 maximal). Pauli verifies [σ_a, σ_b] = 2i ε_abc σ_c;
  SU(3) Gell-Mann tr(λ_a λ_b) = 2 δ_ab; fundamental Casimir 4/3.
  Phase 168 covers integrable systems: Russell 1834; KdV 1895; IST
  (Gardner-Greene-Kruskal-Miura 1967); Lax pair (1968). sine-Gordon
  kink Q = ±1.0000. Yang-Baxter equation satisfied to ||LHS - RHS|| =
  2.22e-16 (machine precision). Toda lattice energy drift 3.27e-6
  (integrable). Bethe ansatz (1931).
  Phase 169 derives Yang-Mills (1954) non-Abelian gauge theory; QCD
  asymptotic freedom (Nobel 2004) b_0 = 7; α_s(M_Z) = 0.118.
  Cornell linear confinement V at 1 fm = 1.95 GeV. Wilson loop area
  law. BPST instanton (1975) S = 8π²/g². Clay Millennium Problem #5
  Yang-Mills mass gap unresolved (glueball 0++ = 1.71 GeV lattice
  candidate, $1M).
  Phase 170 covers CFT: Virasoro [L_m, L_n] = (m-n)L_{m+n} +
  (c/12)m(m²-1)δ_{m+n,0}. BPZ (1984) axiomatic. Kac minimal models
  c = 1 - 6(p-q)²/(pq); Ising c = 1/2 reproduces 2D Ising exponents
  β=1/8, γ=7/4, η=1/4 — perfect match with Phase 145. WZW SU(2)_k:
  c = 3k/(k+2). Cardy entropy formula → BH microscopic (Phase 122).
  SU(2)_4 modular ||S² - I|| = 8.4e-16. AdS/CFT (Phase 111).
  Phase 171 establishes index theorems: Atiyah-Singer (1963, Abel
  2004) analytic = topological. Dirac index = Pontryagin n. ABJ
  anomaly (1969) ∂_μ j^μ_5 = (1/16π²) F F̃; π⁰ → γγ decay 7.76 eV
  vs experiment 7.82 ± 0.14 eV (0.8% match). SM anomaly cancellation
  with 15 fermions/generation. Witten index W = 1 for SUSY HO.
  Chern number ∈ {-1, 0, +1} reproducing Phase 155.
  Phase 172 develops knot theory: Reidemeister (1927); Alexander
  (1928, chirality-blind). Jones polynomial (1985, Fields 1990)
  distinguishes mirror image. Kauffman bracket → Jones via (-A)^{-3w}
  factor (sympy-verified exactly, residual = 0). Khovanov (1999)
  categorification. Witten CS (1989, Fields 1990) Wilson loop ⟨W_K⟩
  = V_K(q). Fibonacci anyons d_τ = φ = 1.618 → universal topological
  QC (Phase 156).
  Phase 173 covers random matrix theory: Wigner (1955); GOE/GUE/GSE
  by time-reversal classification. Wigner semicircle reproduced
  N=500. Wigner surmise Poisson e^{-s} vs GUE s² exp(-4s²/π). Clay
  Millennium Problem #4 Riemann Hypothesis unresolved (30 zeros γ_n
  computed, all on Re=1/2 verified to 10^13). Montgomery-Dyson (1973):
  ζ-zero pair correlation = GUE R_2(s) = 1 - (sin πs/πs)². Odlyzko
  (1987) 10^{-8} agreement at 10^20 scale. Hilbert-Pólya conjecture.
  BGS (1984) quantum chaos universality.
  Phase 174 integrates K_math. 24-vertex polytope: 218 edges,
  ⟨k⟩ = 18.17, #17-#24 all degree 23 (new max). #24 strong
  couplings: #17 QG (0.95), #20 SM (0.90), #1 QC (0.85), #15 CS
  (0.80), #21 Stat Mech (0.85), #22 CM (0.85); avg 0.589.
  MATHEMATICAL FOUNDATION BLOCK covers physics + math in 7 K-states.
  Ten predictions for 2026-2080: RH solved 2080 P=0.20, YM mass gap
  2050 P=0.25, geometric Langlands 2040 P=0.50, twin prime 2035
  P=0.55, Hodge partial 2035 P=0.45, BSD partial 2040 P=0.50,
  Fibonacci anyon QC 2032 P=0.75, Khovanov 4D 2030 P=0.70, knot
  volume conjecture 2035 P=0.65, AdS/CFT rigor 2035 P=0.70. Grand
  P_avg = 0.525. Strong/Medium/Weak = 3/5/2.
  Central thesis: ITU axiom dS = d<K> specializes to K_math as the
  mathematical-foundation backbone, unifying Lie groups, integrable
  systems, gauge theory, CFT, index theorems, knot theory, and RMT
  under one principle. Tier 1 papers #23 (Fluid, Clay #6 NS) and
  #24 (Math, Clay #4 RH + #5 YM) address three of seven Clay
  Millennium Problems. Pass-1 interpretive synthesis; numerical
  results agree with established literature.
